    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1977-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1977-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <head>156. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> to
                    Burmese President <persName corresp="#p_NWE_1">Ne Win</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d156fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, President’s Correspondence with
                        Foreign Leaders File, Box 2, Burma, President <persName corresp="#p_NWE_1">U
                            Ne Win</persName>, 6/77. No classification marking. Thai Prime Minister
                        Thanin Kraiwichian received an identical letter. (Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, President’s Correspondence with
                        Foreign Leaders File, Box 19, Thailand, Prime Minister Thanin Kraiwichian,
                        6/77)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1977-06-15">June 15, 1977</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. President:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I want to express my special thanks and admiration for the deep commitment you
                    have made to deal with the narcotics problem.</p>
                <p>Following his recent visit to your country, Dr. <persName corresp="#p_BPG_1"
                        >Peter Bourne</persName> has told me not only of your determination to deal
                    with this problem, but also of the progress you have already made against both
                    the cultivation and the trafficking of drugs.<note n="2" xml:id="d156fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d155">Document 155</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The entire world community joins in applauding your efforts.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Jimmy Carter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
